This paper is about using Deep Reinforcement Learning to generate text, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves training a Deep Q-Network (DQN) to make decisions, which is a common technique in Artificial Intelligence (AI), making cs.AI the second likely sub-category. The paper also uses Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) networks, which are a type of neural network commonly used in Machine Learning (ML), making cs.LG (Learning) a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves optimizing the DQN using reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of Neural Networks (NE), making cs.NE a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves exploring difficult portions of the input sequence, which is a common technique in Search and Optimization (SD), making cs.SD a possible sub-category.
